# 05 Data Segregation and High-Risk Isolation

## Intent
Reduce blast radius by isolating sensitive identities and high-risk domains.

## Mandatory
- Separate direct identifiers from sensitive attributes where feasible.
- Use pseudonymous identifiers for analytics and non-core workflows.
- Enforce stricter access controls for high-risk categories (mental health, safety, payment-related data).
- Require synthetic/anonymized datasets in non-production environments.

## High-Risk Domain Rules
- Apply stronger review gates and explicit threat modeling.
- Restrict cross-domain joins unless documented and approved.

## Prohibited
- Broad wildcard access to multi-domain sensitive datasets.
- Production dumps in local development.
